<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="84" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,907,1041]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">
<taxonomicName authority="Yin &amp; Kurbatov &amp; Ку, 2022" authorityName="Yin &amp; Kurbatov &amp; Ку" authorityYear="2022" box="[151,288,907,933]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Schmidtinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,288,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Schmidtinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[296,402,907,933]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[296,402,907,933]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is morphologically similar to a number of East Asian genera that are known or putative inquilines of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1804" box="[275,348,943,968]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Lasius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[275,348,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Lasius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ants, 
<emphasis box="[413,447,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">i.e.</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[460,549,943,969]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Songius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[460,549,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Songius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yin &amp; Li" authorityYear="2012" box="[562,650,943,968]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Tangius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[562,650,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Tangius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[709,916,943,969]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Dendrolasiophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[709,916,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Dendrolasiophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. These genera share a similar general structure of the aedeagus, and may form a monophyletic group within Asian 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reitter" authorityYear="1882" box="[922,1022,979,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Batrisini">Batrisini</taxonomicName>
. They can be separated by using the following key:
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="84" type="key">
<key pageId="5" pageNumber="84">
<keyStep pageId="5" pageNumber="84">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1083,1370]" box="[151,1436,1083,1106]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1083,1106]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">
1 Head strongly transverse; each elytron with one basal fovea........................ 
<taxonomicName authority="Nomura, 2010" authorityName="Nomura" authorityYear="2010" box="[1109,1436,1083,1105]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Dendrolasiophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1109,1292,1083,1105]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Dendrolasiophilus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Nomura, S." box="[1298,1436,1084,1105]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" pagination="53 - 60" refId="ref4244" refString="Nomura, S. (2010) A new genus Maajappia and its new species of the subtribe Batrisina, tribe Batrisini (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Pselaphinae) from Japan, with a note on the genus Dendrolasiophilus. Elytra, 38, 53 - 60." type="journal article" year="2010">Nomura, 2010</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1083,1370]" box="[151,1436,1113,1135]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1113,1135]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">- Head almost as long as to slightly longer than wide; each elytron with three basal foveae............................ 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="5" pageNumber="84">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1083,1370]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">
<keyLead pageId="5" pageNumber="84">
2 Sides of tergite 1 (IV) clearly convergent from middle toward base, so base of tergite distinctly..narrower than elytra in their widest part; tergite 
<quantity box="[411,448,1172,1194]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" unit="in" value="1.0">1 in</quantity>
dorsal view markedly longer than 2 (
<collectionCode box="[808,827,1172,1193]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
) and 3 (
<collectionCode box="[906,933,1172,1193]" country="Norway" name="Mykotektet, National Veterinary Institute" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">VI</collectionCode>
) combined............ 
<taxonomicName authority="Yin &amp; Li, 2012" authorityName="Yin &amp; Li" authorityYear="2012" box="[1205,1436,1171,1194]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Tangius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1205,1284,1171,1192]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Tangius</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Yin, Z. - W. &amp; Li, L. - Z. &amp; Zhao, M. - J." box="[1290,1436,1172,1194]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" pagination="55 - 61" refId="ref4995" refString="Yin, Z. - W., Li, L. - Z. &amp; Zhao, M. - J. (2012) Contributions to the knowledge of the myrmecophilous pselaphines (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Pselaphinae) from China. I. Tangius glabellus gen. et sp. nov. from Tibet. Zootaxa, 3397 (1), 55 - 61. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3397.1.4" type="journal article" year="2012">Yin &amp; Li, 2012</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1083,1370]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">
<keyLead pageId="5" pageNumber="84">
- Sides of tergite 1 (IV) broadest at or near base, base of tergite of equal width with or slightly..... broader than elytra at their widest part; tergite 1 (IV) in dorsal view as long as or shorter than 2 (
<collectionCode box="[890,909,1230,1251]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
) and 3 (
<collectionCode box="[988,1015,1230,1251]" country="Norway" name="Mykotektet, National Veterinary Institute" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">VI</collectionCode>
) combined........................ 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="5" pageNumber="84">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1083,1370]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">
<keyLead pageId="5" pageNumber="84">
3 Vertical heights of postocular margins clearly longer than those of eyes; pronotum trapezoidal, broadest at basal 1/3; elytra lacking discal stria; habitus typically stouter............................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="Yin &amp; Li, 2010" authorityName="Yin &amp; Li" authorityYear="2010" box="[1204,1436,1289,1311]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Songius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1204,1284,1289,1310]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Songius</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Yin, Z. - W. &amp; Li, L. - Z. &amp; Zhao, M. - J." box="[1290,1436,1289,1311]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" pagination="241 - 253" refId="ref4835" refString="Yin, Z. - W., Li, L. - Z. &amp; Zhao, M. - J. (2010) Contributions to the knowledge of the myrmecophilous pselaphines (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Pselaphinae) from China. III. Two new genera and two new species of the subtribe Batrisina (Staphylinidae, Pselaphinae, Batrisitae) from a colony of Lasius niger (Hymeptera (sic!), Formicidae, Formicinae) in East China. Sociobiology, 55, 241 - 253." type="journal article" year="2010">Yin &amp; Li, 2010</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1083,1370]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">
<keyLead pageId="5" pageNumber="84">
- Vertical heights of postocular margins shorter than those of eyes; pronotum roundly explanate laterally, broadest near middle; elytra with discal stria; habitus more elongate............................................. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1216,1436,1347,1369]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">
<taxonomicName authority="Yin &amp; Kurbatov &amp; Ку, 2022" authorityName="Yin &amp; Kurbatov &amp; Ку" authorityYear="2022" box="[1216,1340,1347,1369]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Schmidtinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1216,1340,1347,1369]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Schmidtinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1346,1436,1348,1369]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
</key>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="85" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1416,2018]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">
In addition, the new genus differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[640,729,1416,1442]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Songius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[640,729,1416,1442]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Songius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also by a different pattern of male sexual characters, i.e., modified antennae, protibiae, and posterior margin of the metaventrite, which have never been observed in the latter genus. More specifically, all 
<taxonomicName box="[484,663,1488,1514]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis box="[484,573,1488,1514]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Songius</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
have the aedeagus with a more-or-less serrate apical margin of the dorsal lobe, and there is a short apophysis on the lateral margin of the ventral stalk, both of which are lacking in 
<taxonomicName authority="Yin &amp; Kurbatov &amp; Ку, 2022" authorityName="Yin &amp; Kurbatov &amp; Ку" authorityYear="2022" box="[151,288,1560,1586]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Schmidtinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,288,1560,1586]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Schmidtinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[297,403,1560,1586]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[297,403,1560,1586]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yin &amp; Li" authorityYear="2012" box="[412,500,1561,1586]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Tangius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[412,500,1561,1586]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Tangius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
contains two Himalayan species from 
<collectingRegion box="[944,1002,1560,1586]" country="China" name="Xizang" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Tibet</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry box="[1018,1088,1560,1586]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">China</collectingCountry>
) and northern 
<collectingCountry box="[1257,1315,1560,1586]" name="India" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">India</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Yin, Z. - W. &amp; Li, L. - Z." pageId="5" pageNumber="84" pagination="23 - 27" refId="ref4656" refString="Yin, Z. - W. &amp; Li, L. - Z. (2013 b) A new species of Tangius from north India (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Pselaphinae). ZooKeys, 346, 23 - 27. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 346.6233" type="journal article" year="2013">Yin &amp; Li 2013b</bibRefCitation>
); 
<taxonomicName box="[245,334,1596,1622]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Songius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[245,334,1596,1622]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Songius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
consists of four species from 
<collectingRegion box="[671,774,1596,1622]" country="China" name="Zhejiang" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Zhejiang</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[784,861,1597,1623]" country="China" name="Hunan" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Hunan</collectingRegion>
, Guanxi, and was shown to inhabit a much broader distributional range in 
<collectingCountry box="[406,473,1632,1658]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">China</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Yin, Z. - W. &amp; Li, L. - Z." box="[488,660,1632,1659]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" pagination="293 - 300" refId="ref4775" refString="Yin, Z. - W. &amp; Li, L. - Z. (2015) New and little known species of the genus Songius (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Pselaphinae) in China. Zootaxa, 3905 (2), 293 - 300. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3905.2.10" type="journal article" year="2015">Yin &amp; Li 2015</bibRefCitation>
); and 
<taxonomicName box="[727,934,1632,1658]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Dendrolasiophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[727,934,1632,1658]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Dendrolasiophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is represented by four species from Far East 
<collectingCountry box="[151,229,1668,1694]" name="Russia" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Russia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[239,306,1669,1695]" name="Japan" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Japan</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[361,428,1668,1694]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">China</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Nomura, S." box="[441,600,1668,1694]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" pagination="133 - 148" refId="ref4204" refString="Nomura, S. (2008) A new genus Dendrolasiophilus and a new synonym in the subtribe Batrisina, tribe Batrisini (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Pselaphinae) from Japan. Elytra, 36, 133 - 148." type="journal article" year="2008">Nomura 2008</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Nomura, S." box="[609,669,1668,1694]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" pagination="53 - 60" refId="ref4244" refString="Nomura, S. (2010) A new genus Maajappia and its new species of the subtribe Batrisina, tribe Batrisini (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Pselaphinae) from Japan, with a note on the genus Dendrolasiophilus. Elytra, 38, 53 - 60." type="journal article" year="2010">2010</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Yin, Z. - W. &amp; Li, L. - Z." box="[678,854,1668,1694]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" pagination="183 - 187" refId="ref4566" refString="Yin, Z. - W. &amp; Li, L. - Z. (2013 a) Dendrolasiophilus wenhsini (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Pselaphinae), a new myrmecophilous batrisine associated with Lasius (Dendrolasius) spathepus from Guangxi, South China. In: Lin, M. - Y. &amp; Chen, C. - C. (Eds.). In memory of Mr. Wenhsin Lin. Formosa Ecological Company, New Taipei City, pp. 183 - 187." type="book chapter" year="2013">Yin &amp; Li 2013a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kurbatov, S. A. &amp; Kovalev, A. V." box="[864,1164,1668,1694]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" pagination="296 - 300" refId="ref4069" refString="Kurbatov, S. A. &amp; Kovalev, A. V. (2022) A new species of the genus Dendrolasiophilus Nomura, 2010 from the south of the Russian Far East (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Pselaphinae). Zootaxa, 5100 (2), 296 - 300. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 5100.2.9" type="journal article" year="2022">Kurbatov &amp; Kovalev 2022</bibRefCitation>
). All members of the latter three genera variably possess a suite of ‘reductive’ (
<bibRefCitation author="Parker, J. &amp; Owens, B." box="[767,1021,1704,1730]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" pagination="219 - 229" refId="ref4292" refString="Parker, J. &amp; Owens, B. (2018) Batriscydmaenus Parker and Owens, new genus, and convergent evolution of a &quot; reductive &quot; ecomorph in socially symbiotic Pselaphinae (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). Coleopterists Bulletin, 72, 219 - 229. https: // doi. org / 10.1649 / 0010 - 065 X- 72.2.219" type="journal article" year="2018">Parker &amp; Owens 2018</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Yin, Z. - W." box="[1032,1137,1704,1730]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" pagination="233 - 240" refId="ref4458" refString="Yin, Z. - W. (2018) Loeblibatrus Yin, a new genus of myrmecophilous Pselaphinae (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae) from southern China. Coleopterists Bulletin, 72, 233 - 240. https: // doi. org / 10.1649 / 0010 - 065 X- 72.2.233" type="journal article" year="2018">Yin 2018</bibRefCitation>
) morphological traits such as a smooth and glabrous appearance, moniliform antennomeres, a reduced number of foveae, carinae and sulcus on the body surface, and have developed gland-associated trichomes at the posterior corners of the head. Some of these characters are found in 
<taxonomicName authority="Yin &amp; Kurbatov &amp; Ку, 2022" authorityName="Yin &amp; Kurbatov &amp; Ку" authorityYear="2022" box="[478,615,1812,1838]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Schmidtinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[478,615,1812,1838]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Schmidtinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[622,727,1812,1838]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[622,727,1812,1838]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, which suggests that it can be likewise a myrmecophilic genus. Almost each species of this group is represented by such few specimens in collections that continuing field efforts are needed to further explore the biology and evolutionary history of these beetles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1416,2018]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,151,249]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="85" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">
There are a few other recently described batrisine genera from 
<collectingCountry box="[896,999,1920,1947]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">East Asia</collectingCountry>
that host different ant genera and show morphological peculiarities related to myrmecophily, e.g., 
<taxonomicName authority="Yin &amp; Li" authorityName="Yin &amp; Li" box="[817,1104,1956,1982]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pengzhongiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[817,991,1956,1982]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Pengzhongiella</emphasis>
Yin &amp; Li
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1804" box="[1122,1292,1956,1982]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Odontomachus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1122,1292,1956,1982]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Odontomachus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Yin" authorityName="Yin" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lisubatrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1316,1436,1956,1982]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Lisubatrus</emphasis>
Yin
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Yin" authorityName="Yin" box="[206,395,1992,2018]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Loeblibatrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[206,349,1992,2018]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Loeblibatrus</emphasis>
Yin
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1867" box="[412,586,1993,2018]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ectomomyrmex" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[412,586,1993,2018]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Ectomomyrmex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and 
<taxonomicName authority="Yin &amp; Li" authorityName="Yin &amp; Li" box="[657,922,1992,2018]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Myrmicophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[657,816,1992,2018]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Myrmicophila</emphasis>
Yin &amp; Li
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1804" box="[939,1040,1993,2018]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Myrmica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[939,1040,1993,2018]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Myrmica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Yin, Z. - W. &amp; Li, L. - Z." box="[1064,1245,1992,2018]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" pagination="17 - 26" refId="ref4711" refString="Yin, Z. - W. &amp; Li, L. - Z. (2013 c) Pengzhongiella daicongchaoi gen. et sp. n., a remarkable myrmecophile (Staphylinidae, Pselaphinae, Batrisitae) from the Gaoligong Mountains. ZooKeys, 326, 17 - 26. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 326.5933" type="journal article" year="2013">Yin &amp; Li 2013c</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Yin, Z. - W." box="[1256,1362,1992,2018]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" pagination="593 - 601" refId="ref4400" refString="Yin, Z. - W. (2017) Lisubatrus dongzhiweii gen. et sp. nov. from the Gaoligong Mountains, China (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Pselaphinae). Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae, 57, 593 - 601. https: // doi. org / 10.1515 / aemnp- 2017 - 0091" type="journal article" year="2017">Yin 2017</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Yin, Z. - W." box="[1373,1432,1992,2018]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" pagination="233 - 240" refId="ref4458" refString="Yin, Z. - W. (2018) Loeblibatrus Yin, a new genus of myrmecophilous Pselaphinae (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae) from southern China. Coleopterists Bulletin, 72, 233 - 240. https: // doi. org / 10.1649 / 0010 - 065 X- 72.2.233" type="journal article" year="2018">2018</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Yin, Z. - W." box="[151,210,151,177]" pageId="6" pageNumber="85" pagination="684 - 688" refId="ref4509" refString="Yin, Z. - W. (2021) A new species of the rare myrmecophilous genus Myrmicophila Yin and Li from Xizang, China (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Pselaphinae). Coleopterists Bulletin, 75, 684 - 688. https: // doi. org / 10.1649 / 0010 - 065 X- 75.3.684" type="journal article" year="2021">2021</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Yin, Z. - W. &amp; Li, L. - Z. &amp; Zhao, M. - J." box="[220,386,151,177]" pageId="6" pageNumber="85" pagination="175 - 183" refId="ref4928" refString="Yin, Z. - W., Li, L. - Z. &amp; Zhao, M. - J. (2011) Contributions to the knowledge of the myrmecophilous pselaphines (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Pselaphinae) from China. VIII. Myrmicophila tangliangi, a new genus and species of Batrisini from Yunnan. Sociobiology, 58, 175 - 183." type="journal article" year="2011">
Yin 
<emphasis box="[267,315,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="85">et al</emphasis>
. 2011
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Zhang, W. - X. &amp; Yin, Z. - W." box="[397,609,151,177]" pageId="6" pageNumber="85" pagination="129 - 136" refId="ref5076" refString="Zhang, W. - X. &amp; Yin, Z. - W. (2022) Two new species of myrmecophilous Pselaphinae from China (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). Revue suisse de Zoologie, 129, 129 - 136. https: // doi. org / 10.35929 / RSZ. 0067" type="journal article" year="2022">Zhang &amp; Yin 2022</bibRefCitation>
). They are morphologically distinct from the 
<taxonomicName box="[1111,1318,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Dendrolasiophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1111,1318,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="85">Dendrolasiophilus</emphasis>
